A rectangular garden shares one side with one side of a house. An adjacent side of the garden is eight feet long. If the area of the garden is 184 square feet, what is the length, in feet, of the common side?
inference:
Let the length of the common side be $x$ feet.
The adjacent side of the garden is 8 feet long.
The area of the garden is given as 184 square feet.
The area of a rectangle is given by the product of its length and width.
In this case, the area is $x \times 8 = 184$.
$8x = 184$
$x = \frac{184}{8}$
$x = 23$
Final Answer: $\boxed{23}$ I hope it is correct.
ground_truth:
The area of the garden is the product of the sides.  So the common side must be

$$\frac{184}{8}=\boxed{23}$$

feet.
